# Rewrite the projects section — remove placeholder cards

## Context

`index.html` is a single-file personal page. Its "What I'm working on" section (index.html:225-235) currently contains two placeholder cards — "Project One" and "Project Two" — both linking to `#` with filler descriptions. The user wants that section rewritten with the placeholders gone, and the page kept as one self-contained file.

## Approach

Edit only the `<section>` at index.html:225-235. Replace the two placeholder `<a class="card">` elements with a short prose paragraph so the section stays meaningful without inventing fake projects:

```html
<section>
  <h2>What I'm working on</h2>
  <p class="section-note">
    I'm always tinkering on something new. The best place to see what's
    current is my <a href="https://github.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a> —
    real projects will be listed here as they ship.
  </p>
</section>
```

Add one small style rule alongside the existing section styles (near the `.card` block, which stays in place for future use — or is deleted, see cleanup note):

```css
.section-note {
  font-size: 16px;
  color: var(--muted);
  max-width: 60ch;
}
.section-note a {
  color: var(--accent);
  text-decoration: none;
}
.section-note a:hover {
  text-decoration: underline;
}
```

### CSS cleanup

With both cards removed, the `.card`, `.card:hover`, `.card h3`, and `.card p` rules (index.html:112-140) become unused. Since these orphans are created by this change, remove them per the surgical-changes guideline. Everything else (skills, links, footer) is untouched.

## Files

- `index.html` — only file modified; no new files created.

## Verification

Open the file in a browser (`open index.html`) and confirm:
1. "Project One" / "Project Two" cards are gone.
2. The section renders the new prose with a working GitHub link.
3. Skills, contact, and footer sections are unaffected.
4. No stray `.card` CSS remains (grep for `card` in the file).

